  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ABank-Banking on Women</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The key development objective of this project is to increase financial inclusion in Turkey. The project is designed to improve access to finance for SMEs in Turkey, with a special focus on women owned businesses (at least 50% of the project amount will be used to on-lend to women owned SMEs). By working with ABank, a well-run, mid-tier bank with a particular focus on SMEs, this project is intended to demonstrate the business opportunity presented by women entrepreneurs as an under-served market.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project is comprised of a senior loan investment in Alternatifbank A.S. (ABank or the Bank) of up to $25,000,000 which would be used to support women-owned small and medium enterprises (SME) and SMEs in general in Turkey.</narrative>
  </description>
